com.esri.mo2.util
Class BasePropertiesResourceFileLocator

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.esri.mo2.util.BasePropertiesResourceFileLocator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, PropertiesFileLocator
public class BasePropertiesResourceFileLocator
extends Object
implements PropertiesFileLocator

Consists of a single resource file that contains references to other resource files. Entries in the resource file must consist of a key that is a unique integer number, with a value that is the name of another resource file.

The number can be any integer number, as long as no other entry has the same number. After all entries have been read from the properties file, they will be sorted in the numeric order of the integer key - that will be the order that is returned by the getFilenames() method.

The name specifies the resource location of another resource file. This must include the full resource pathname, relative to a class that is specified in the BasePropertiesResourceFileLocator(Class,String) constructor, or is relative to the BasePropertiesResourceFileLocator class itself, if you use the other constructor.

Here is an example, note that the entries need not be specified in numeric order, nor does there have to be a complete series of numbers - you can leave some out if you like - but you do have to ensure there are no duplicate numbers.


 	# GeoCodeStyles.properties
 	3: /com/esri/mo2/res/props/USAddressZ.properties
 	0: /com/esri/mo2/res/props/USAddress.properties
 	1: /com/esri/mo2/res/props/Zip5.properties

In the above example, the getFilenames() method will yield an array of 3 strings containing:


 	"/com/esri/mo2/res/props/USAddress.properties"
 	"/com/esri/mo2/res/props/Zip5.properties"
 	"/com/esri/mo2/res/props/USAddressZ.properties"
